            <h2 class="title-blog" >Top 5 outstanding tourist attractions in Dalat</h2>
            <section class="section1">
                <h3>Datanla Waterfall Tourist Area</h3>
                <p>
                    Datanla is one of the great waterfalls of beautiful Da Lat, a tourist destination that is loved by many tourists. Datanla waterfall Da Lat still retains its characteristic poetic wildness. Visitors coming here are not only overwhelmed by the poetic beauty of Datanla waterfall but also are adventurous with interesting games such as skateboarding here.
                    If you go to feel strong and happy, you have to go in the off season, because going away from the person in front and relaxing is like playing a roller coaster.
                </p>
                <img src="https://cdn.justfly.vn/1920x1280/media/202112/14/1639471497-thac-datanla-da-lat.jpg" alt="">
                <h3>Valleys love</h3>
                <p>
                    Located less than 5km from the center of Da Lat city to the East - North. Valley of Love is not only a romantic destination for couples when traveling, but also attracts all visitors by its enchanting beauty and charming mountains.
                    This is the gathering place of small streams flowing from high mountains to the clear Da Thien Lake, winding around a valley lined with green pine trees. With an area of ​​​​nearly 140 hectares, with a cool and fresh climate, beautiful and charming natural landscapes, the valley of love will definitely bring visitors unforgettable experiences.
                </p>
                <img src="https://cdn.justfly.vn/1920x1314/media/202112/14/1639447917-thung-lung-tinh-yeu-du-lich-da-lat.jpg" alt="">
                <h3>Langbiang Peak</h3>
                <p>
                    LangBiang Mountain is a place to go to enjoy the fresh and quiet air when coming to Da Lat. In addition, there are regular tours and gong bonfire festivals that are very fun at night. To get to the top of the mountain, visitors have to ride a Jeep up,
                    Up above you can zoom in to see the natural scenery here! Visitors up here mainly take pictures to check in. If you have time, sitting at the shop making a cup of warm tea or something hot is also quite chill.
                </p>
                <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/84/%C4%90%E1%BB%89nh_Langbiang.JPG" alt="">
                <h3>Dalat Railway Station</h3>
                <p>
                    With a route of 7 km, the train will take visitors to explore the mountain town. Although the speed is very slow and the locomotive is loud, this is the attraction of the station for tourists to visit and admire along the way. The last point to visit is Linh Phuoc Pagoda - or Ve Chai Pagoda - a unique Buddhist architecture and explore Trai Mat town.
                    In addition to those who do not like to take the train, this train station also has railway tracks and wildflower fields that are suitable for taking photos. Especially in the seasons of wild sunflowers, tortoiseshells, guava brooches, etc., the whole station area becomes colorful and extremely suitable for you to "live virtual".
                </p>
                <img src="https://media-cdn-v2.laodong.vn/storage/newsportal/2020/1/31/781396/Ga_Da_Lat_17_Zing_1.jpg" alt="">
                <h3>Lam Vien Square</h3>
                <p>
                    Referring to Lam Vien square, the first thing to mention is the "legendary" giant wild sunflower, with a height of more than 18m, an area of ​​​​1200 m2, outside covered with thousands of colorful stained glass panels. inside is a performing arts place with 1,500 seats. There is also a beautifully designed cafe and bar inside.
                    Not far from the giant wild sunflower, there is also a giant artichoke flower - another symbol of Lam Vien. This flower bud has a height of 15m, also designed entirely of stained glass, braided in is now a coffee shop with an area of ​​​​about 1,500m2. This will be a great place for you to stop,
                    Sip a cup of coffee and admire the beautiful scenery of Xuan Huong Lake after having fun and sightseeing around the square.
                </p>
